                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/2781</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-16T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 17, 2.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. I understand that the deportations from Brussels will begin within a short
                    time. They continue here and there in the country, <pb facs="0845" n="673"
                        xml:id="pg_673"/> though with diminished frequency, and we are told with
                    milder methods. The civil government is still trying to have the policy
                    abrogated but has not yet succeeded in impressing its views upon the military
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
